issue.title: Reduce lock contention in Thread.getAndClearInterrupt

repository.name: openj9-openjdk-jdk
repository.description: Extensions for OpenJDK for Eclipse OpenJ9

issue.body:
Lock contention in `Thread.getAndClearInterrupt` is reduced by
acquiring the lock only when the value of the `Thread.interrupted`
field is `true`.

Related: https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/20414

issue.title: Add synchronization for Class.allPermissionsPD

repository.name: openj9
repository.description: Eclipse OpenJ9: A Java Virtual Machine for OpenJDK that's optimized for small footprint, fast start-up, and high throughput.   Builds on Eclipse OMR (https://github.com/eclipse/omr) and combines with the Extensions for OpenJDK for OpenJ9 repo.

issue.body:
Synchronization has been added to ensure safe initialization and safe
publication of `Class.allPermissionsPD`. This addresses the locking
contention on `Class.allPermissionsPD` in `Class.getProtectionDomain()`.

Fixes: #20351

timeline_data.body: This problem can still occur; see https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/pull/21073#pullrequestreview-2598751649.

issue.title: Use a nested holder class to store allPermissionsPD

repository.name: openj9
repository.description: Eclipse OpenJ9: A Java Virtual Machine for OpenJDK that's optimized for small footprint, fast start-up, and high throughput.   Builds on Eclipse OMR (https://github.com/eclipse/omr) and combines with the Extensions for OpenJDK for OpenJ9 repo.

issue.body:
Using this approach, `allPermissionsPD` can be a final field. VM's class
initialization mechanisms will prevent races via the `static` block.

Fixes: #20351
